Unless I&#x27;m misreading this, there&#x27;s a slight semantic difference between the two cases: with the GADT-based interpreter, an if expression&#x27;s two branches must both evaluate to integers:<p><pre><code>  | GIf : bool expr&#x27; * int expr&#x27; * int expr&#x27; -> int expr&#x27;
</code></pre>
...whereas in the original both branches could evaluate to bools (or even totally separate types). Do you need a separate case for each type, or could one write something like the following?<p><pre><code>  | GIf : bool expr&#x27; * a expr&#x27; * a expr&#x27; -> a expr&#x27;</code></pre>
